<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-151-430 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 957 954</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  May 20 1991 v8 n10 p78(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FGIC: a case study in success. (Financial Guaranty InsuranceCompany)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Chivvis, Andrei M.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Federal Guaranty Insurance Company (FGIC) made the decision todownsize from a mainframe environment to a local-area network(LAN) when it became apparent that the system on which it hadrelied since 1987 was no longer capable of meeting its needs,either in terms of capacity or the ability to handleever-increasing amounts of information in a constantly shrinkingtimeframe.andP;  The decision was made to implement a LAN comprised ofhardware based on Intel's 80386 microprocessor, running onNovell's Netware network operating system.andP;  The Foxpro databasemanagement system (DBMS) serves as the basis for five interlinkedapplications used to analyze and track municipal bond insurancepolicies.andP;  FGIC's downsizing efforts have yielded rich rewards interms of greater productivity, cost savings, and streamlinedoperations.andP;  While the size of FGIC's portfolio increased by 40percent, its cost of operations decreased by 80 percent.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Financial Guaranty Insurance Co. (Automation).andO;Topic:     Case StudySystem ConversionEconomics of ComputingTrendsManagement of EDP.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>